<h2><strong>What&rsquo;s Inside</strong><br />
&nbsp;</h2>

<p>This guide is intended to describe the important parts of cryptocurrency without a lot of huge technical terms. You can learn about Bitcoin and Ethereum, including what they are, how they work, and why they&rsquo;re such a big deal in the cryptocurrency space. By the end, you&rsquo;ll know <a href="https://www.coinmama.com/guide/cryptocurrency-mining">what &ldquo;cryptocurrency mining&rdquo; is</a>, how it relates to &ldquo;Proof of Work&rdquo; and &ldquo;Proof of Stake&rdquo;, how they work, and the advantages of one over another.</p>

<p>If you decide that you want to go beyond learning about cryptocurrency and want to get involved, everything that you need to get started is included as well. You can find a guide explaining <a href="https://www.coinmama.com/guide/how-to-get-cryptocurrency">what a cryptocurrency &ldquo;wallet&rdquo; is</a>, how to get one, and how to buy your first cryptocurrency and make sure it makes it inside. For investors, there is a section on <a href="https://www.coinmama.com/guide/cryptocurrency-investment-strategies">basic investment strategies</a> for cryptocurrencies and the pros and cons of day trading versus long-term holding. Finally, you can find out <a href="https://www.coinmama.com/guide/what-is-an-ico">what an ICO is</a> and the options and opportunities it offers to potential investors.<br />
&nbsp;</p>

